{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17480469","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17480469"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T23:44:09+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T23:44:09+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"57"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"57","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/57"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.56,0.14,0.1,0.06,0.14]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"57"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76414"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"57","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/57"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"57"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61911"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"5"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"134"},{"type":"tags","id":"1051"},{"type":"tags","id":"1151"},{"type":"tags","id":"1198"},{"type":"tags","id":"1412"},{"type":"tags","id":"3348"},{"type":"tags","id":"4962"},{"type":"tags","id":"4964"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"31600"},{"type":"contributions","id":"41972"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43780"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76414","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/76414"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 36-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic for review of persistent epigastric pain. She initially presented two months ago with epigastric pain worse with eating, associated with nausea and heartburn and was commenced on a proton pump inhibitor. She has no significant medical history and takes no other regular medications.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EInitial endoscopy showed multiple ulcers in the gastric antrum, pylorus and duodenum. A rapid urease test was positive for \u003Cem\u003EHelicobacter pylori\u003C/em\u003E. She completed 14 days of triple therapy (esomeprazole, clarithromycin and amoxicillin) followed by two weeks of esomeprazole alone.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. Her abdomen is soft with mild epigastric tenderness. A faecal antigen test confirms \u003Cem\u003EH. pylori\u003C/em\u003E eradication, but repeat endoscopy shows persistent ulceration.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate next investigation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Fasting serum gastrin level","Bismuth quadruple therapy","Secretin stimulation test","Four week triple therapy course","Double dose proton pump inhibitor"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with multiple gastric and duodenal ulcers that persist despite successful \u003Cem\u003EH. pylori\u003C/em\u003E eradication, raising suspicion for Zollinger-Ellison syndrome (ZES), which is caused by a gastrin-secreting neuroendocrine tumour (gastrinoma).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFasting serum gastrin level\u003C/strong\u003E is the most appropriate initial investigation for suspected gastrinoma. A level more than ten times the upper limit of normal is diagnostic of ZES, while lesser elevations require further investigation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esecretin stimulation test\u003C/strong\u003E is used to confirm the diagnosis of gastrinoma after an elevated fasting gastrin is found, but it is not the appropriate first-line test.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBismuth quadruple therapy\u003C/strong\u003E would be appropriate for \u003Cem\u003EH. pylori\u003C/em\u003E treatment failure, but this patient has documented successful eradication. Similarly, \u003Cstrong\u003Efour week triple therapy\u003C/strong\u003E would not be appropriate as \u003Cem\u003EH. pylori\u003C/em\u003E has already been successfully eradicated.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDouble dose proton pump inhibitor\u003C/strong\u003E therapy may provide symptom relief but does not address the underlying diagnosis. High-dose proton pump inhibitors should be continued while awaiting gastrin results.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOther causes of refractory peptic ulcer disease include medication non-compliance and continued use of ulcerogenic medications (NSAIDs, aspirin). However, the presence of multiple ulcers in different locations strongly suggests ZES as the underlying cause.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Multiple gastric and duodenal ulcers that persist after Helicobacter pylori eradication should raise suspicion for Zollinger-Ellison syndrome.","Fasting serum gastrin is the initial test of choice for suspected gastrinoma.","Secretin stimulation testing is a confirmatory test for gastrinoma after elevated fasting gastrin is found."],"references":["Napolitano L. Refractory Peptic Ulcer Disease. Gastroenterol Clin N Am. 2009; 38:267-88. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19446258/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61911"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"57"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61911","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/61911"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-03T13:38:29+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-03T13:38:30+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"dat